<h1>@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}</h1>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}} is used to indicate a motion in a direction towards from the speaker's point of view.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^day}}hamada@KJ{{new^listen}}ga@KJ{{come}}nai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Today's newspaper hasn't come yet.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}} can also be used to describe motion towards a place where the speaker has placed his point of view.
In this example, the speaker did not attend the party and is taking the viewpoint of the listener.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{nanshi-}}hakinou@KT{{pa-texi-}}ni@KJ{{come}}mashitaka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Did Nancy come to the party yesterday?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>
</p>

